Albert Edwin Hawksley Sangwine (16 March 1901 – 3 November 1962) was an English freestyle sport wrestler who competed for Great Britain in the 1924 Summer Olympics.He was born in Tottenham and died in Chingford.
In 1924 he finished tenth in the freestyle heavyweight tournament.
At the 1930 Empire Games he won the silver medal in the freestyle heavyweight class.
